{Syntax:}\par similarity(Point, Realk, Angle, Object)\par
\par Dilates and rotates a geometric object about the same center point.\par
{\par Example:}\par similarity(0, 3, angle(0,1,i),point(2,0)) dilates the point at (2,0) by a scale factor of 3 (a point at (6,0)), then rotates the result 90\u176? counterclockwise to create a point at (0, 6)\par }